  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nThe rook main entry point binary crashes with the following while I'm trying to upgrade the Kubernetes references to 1.13 as described in #2806:\r\n```\r\n/usr/local/bin/rook flag redefined: log_dir\r\npanic: /usr/local/bin/rook flag redefined: log_dir\r\n\r\ngoroutine 1 [running]:\r\nflag.(*FlagSet).Var(0xc0000ac180, 0x1ed2b40, 0xc0003f6120, 0x1c619e5, 0x7, 0x1cadde7, 0x2f)\r\n\t/usr/local/go/src/flag/flag.go:805 +0x529\r\nflag.(*FlagSet).StringVar(0xc0000ac180, 0xc0003f6120, 0x1c619e5, 0x7, 0x0, 0x0, 0x1cadde7, 0x2f)\r\n\t/usr/local/go/src/flag/flag.go:708 +0x8a\r\nflag.(*FlagSet).String(0xc0000ac180, 0x1c619e5, 0x7, 0x0, 0x0, 0x1cadde7, 0x2f, 0xc0003f6110)\r\n\t/usr/local/go/src/flag/flag.go:721 +0x8b\r\nflag.String(0x1c619e5, 0x7, 0x0, 0x0, 0x1cadde7, 0x2f, 0x0)\r\n\t/usr/local/go/src/flag/flag.go:728 +0x69\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe cause appears to be the EdgeFS operator's single usage of `glog`: https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/utils.go#L24\r\n\r\n`glog` should not be used directly by the Rook operators, instead the consistent logger pattern shown here should be used instead: https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/pkg/operator/ceph/cluster/controller.go#L65\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** Rook binary not to crash/panic\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\nNot a direct/easy repo since this requires updating the Rook dependencies to k8s 1.13, and i'm not sure why that triggers this issue.  However, we should be using a consistent logger scheme throughout all the operators, and this should be an easy change to stop using `glog` in EdgeFS (it's only used in 1 place) and follow the same convention the other operators use.",
